        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer105510946" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6315899108515972923">If you&apos;ve seen Mizoguchi&apos;s Ugetsu then you know not to expect horror stories from this collection. But hey haven&apos;t you seen all those Asian horror flicks?, you&apos;ll ask. That&apos;s scary stuff! Yes, but the way they scare you is they get under your skin and then grow aliens in your brain. These are a bit more subtle. Symbolic, atmospheric and rooted in tradition, the stories won&apos;t give you nightmares if you read them before bedtime, just a twinge that there&apos;s a world out there beyond the touchable. </span>
  <span id="freeText6315899108515972923" style="display:none">If you've seen Mizoguchi's Ugetsu then you know not to expect horror stories from this collection. But hey haven't you seen all those Asian horror flicks?, you'll ask. That's scary stuff! Yes, but the way they scare you is they get under your skin and then grow aliens in your brain. These are a bit more subtle. Symbolic, atmospheric and rooted in tradition, the stories won't give you nightmares if you read them before bedtime, just a twinge that there's a world out there beyond the touchable. </span>
