<div id="review_2390559004" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2390559004" />
    <a title="Akemi G." class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/28637268-akemi-g"><img alt="Akemi G." src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442980095p2/28637268.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2390559004?book_show_action=true">May 13, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Akemi G." class="user" itemprop="url" name="Akemi G." href="/user/show/28637268-akemi-g">Akemi G.</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/28637268-akemi-g?shelf=japanese-lit">japanese-lit</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/28637268-akemi-g?shelf=read-fiction">read-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/28637268-akemi-g?shelf=short-stories">short-stories</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2390559004" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8438332356554422653">Nine short ghost fantasies. <br/><br/>Perhaps it would help some readers to understand that the author had to be politically correct (by the standards of his days), at least superficially, for his books to be published in the feudal society. Therefore, the story that involves the former emperor had to be placed first--even though the second bromance story is probably the best. (Note that same sex relationships were nothing to be hidden.) Some stories sound sexist for the same reason. For instance, the sto</span>
  <span id="freeText8438332356554422653" style="display:none">Nine short ghost fantasies. <br /><br />Perhaps it would help some readers to understand that the author had to be politically correct (by the standards of his days), at least superficially, for his books to be published in the feudal society. Therefore, the story that involves the former emperor had to be placed first--even though the second bromance story is probably the best. (Note that same sex relationships were nothing to be hidden.) Some stories sound sexist for the same reason. For instance, the story about a loyal wife who, after death, kills her husband's lover and the husband. While there are lines that condemn women's "jealousy," it should be clear that the real intent is to caution men about their excessive lust. <br /><br />Akinari was a doctor and scholar of Japanese classic literature. He also read Chinese literature widely. The stories here are his modern adaptations of various older stories, in the form of historical fiction. For this reason, non-Japanese readers might have some challenges, but the book seems to come with notes. <br /><br />Ultimately, there are two kinds of ghost stories, depending on how the author sees <b>our mortality</b>: the ones that see ghosts as our extension and the ones that treat them as merely weird beings. <br /><br /><i>Read in Japanese.</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="8438332356554422653" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


