<div id="review_3805407699" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3805407699" />
    <a title="Lynn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3027890-lynn"><img alt="Lynn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1276121725p2/3027890.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3805407699?book_show_action=true">Feb 17, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lynn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lynn" href="/user/show/3027890-lynn">Lynn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/19489200-tales-of-moonlight-and-rain">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3805407699" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2639048298965870359"><strong>Not Engaging. </strong><br/><br/>I’ve read Rashomon and collected stories and really enjoyed them. I was hoping to enjoy this as well. The stories in this translation doesn’t seem poetic or magical. It seems more academic and everything is spelled out laboriously. I don’t know if other translations are more interesting but this landed with a thud for me. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


